title: The SpaceX Rocket Launch Has Been Abruptly Cancelled
text:
The SpaceX Rocket Launch Has Been Abruptly Cancelled 
The launch may be rescheduled for tomorrow. AP By Associated Press and Marcia Dunn Feb 18, 2017 SpaceX will have to wait at least another day to launch from NASA's historic moon pad. Last-minute rocket trouble forced SpaceX to halt Saturday's countdown at Florida's Kennedy Space Center. The unmanned Falcon rocket remains at Launch Complex 39A, waiting to soar on a space station delivery mission. It's the same pad where Americans flew to the moon almost a half-century ago, and where the shuttle program ended in 2011. Advertisement - Continue Reading Below This will be SpaceX's first Florida launch since a rocket explosion last summer. The next launch attempt could come as early as Sunday morning.
